Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Librarian Victoria , BC Description Camosun College invites applications from qualified candidates for the role of Librarian. Responsibilities will include: Providing reference services in traditional and virtual contexts including AskAwayProviding library orientations and information literacy workshop &amp; classesDeveloping online guides and learning objectsSupporting instructors and staff with discovery and databases/digital resourcesLiaising with faculty in assigned areas in regards to accessing and acquiring learning and curricular resourcesCollection development in an assigned areaContributing to the communication and marketing of library services and resourcesparticipating in projects beyond the library and in collaboration with the professional and local communitiesThe following is required for successful employment as a member of the Library team:A demonstrated commitment to the scholarship of teaching and learningActive participation in our learner centered environment while promoting excellence in library services and resourcesCommitment to current and trending philosophies, practices and advancementsAdherence to, and compliance with teaching related policies, procedures and protocolsA willingness to serve on departmental, school and/or organizational committeesEngaged participation in professional development activities that contribute to the goals of the department, school and the CollegeA consistent demonstration of excellence and respect in verbal and written communicationsAn ability to contribute to and cultivate collegial and collaborative work relationshipsComfort and proficiency with educational technology and MS Office programs such as Outlook, Word, ExcelCapable of thriving in a BC post-secondary education setting that’s welcoming and relevant to Indigenous learners and helping to prepare non-Indigenous students, graduates and employees to better understand, live alongside of, and work with Indigenous peoplesA commitment to sustainable practices within our environment and societyKnowledge Skills and Abilities: Broad knowledge of current academic library service issuesExperienced in providing reference service in person and virtuallyExperienced in creating instructional and research materials in a variety of formats including LibGuidesThe ability to teach a range of library related subjects to learners with varying needs and experience in a variety of learning environmentsDemonstrated knowledge of pedagogy, including the ability to adapt instruction to student needsDemonstrated ability to communicate effectively with users from a wide variety of cultural and linguistic backgrounds.Demonstrated knowledge of a range of library and educational technologies including institutional repositories, integrated library systems, discovery systems and learning management systemsDemonstrated knowledge of electronic, print and media resources appropriate for a comprehensive community collegeDemonstrated knowledge of the full lifecycle of electronic resources, from acquisition and access to troubleshooting and assessmentKnowledgeable about scholarly communication including copyright, open education resources, and open access publishingExcellent interpersonal &amp; an ability to contribute to and cultivate collegial and collaborative work relationshipsStrong ability to take initiative and complete tasks as assignedQualificationsMaster’s degree from an ALA-accredited schoolTwo years recent library experienceMinimum of one year of teaching, training or instructional experience (preferably at the post-secondary level).To applyPlease apply to this posting by visiting our website: https://camosun.peopleadmin.ca/postings/5649 Compensation $61,596 - $98,978 per year Closes: 18 May, 2023 Camosun College Victoria , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.