Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Administrative &amp; Support Services Assistant Kamloops , BC Description About the Thompson-Nicola Regional DistrictEncompassing an unparalleled geographic region in the heart of British Columbia, the Thompson-Nicola Regional District (TNRD) offers the best of both worlds. Urban life within vibrant communities and outlying rural regions showcase the region's beauty: pristine but rugged mountains, rolling grasslands, lush evergreen forests and both historic and modern areas, all within approximately 45,000 square kilometres. Headquartered in the City of Kamloops, the TNRD provides a wide range of local government services to a population of 144,000 located within its 11 diverse municipalities and 10 electoral areas. Our Library SystemThe Thompson-Nicola Regional Library (TNRL), the biggest department of the Regional District provides services through 12 locations, a Mobile Library and Library Home Service. Located in the Central Interior of British Columbia, the TNRL is committed to providing excellent service to patrons for lifetime personal growth, learning and enjoyment. The Library team provides programming, materials and resources to people of all ages and abilities. The Administrative &amp; Support Services Assistant will work in an organization that values flexibility and exemplary service. As a member of the TNRL, you will support the library in building strong relationships and partnerships in all of our communities. The RoleReporting to the Chief Librarian, the Administrative &amp; Support Services Assistant, provides administrative support to the library’s leadership team. Administrative duties include booking and scheduling assistance, preparing and processing correspondence, and distributing mail, coordinating meetings and events, recording and distributing minutes, records management (electronic &amp; paper), locating vendors, sourcing prices, placing approved orders, following up on problem orders and coordinating delivery of supply and capital items to libraries. This position also provides support on special projects by researching, compiling and summarizing information. Gathers and prepares statistics and information for reports etc. The Administrative &amp; Support Services Assistant also provides back-up for Support Services which may include receiving and processing of materials, and Interlibrary Loans. Some travel may be required for special events.The Schedule - Monday to Friday - 8:30am to 4:00pm JOB REQUIREMENTSThe Ideal Candidate will have:• A passion for helping others and a belief in the importance of literacy• Minimum two-year Diploma from an accredited post-secondary institution• Excellent interpersonal, organizational &amp; time management skills• Demonstrated attention to detail and planning skills• Ability to communicate effectively, both verbally and in writing, with people from all levels of the organization• Sound judgment and problem solving skills• Self-starter with the ability to work independently and as part of a team• Flexibility in responding to changing work demands • Ability to quickly learn new skills • Ability to handle information discretely • Demonstrated computer skills (must be proficient with Microsoft Office Suite)• Experience in meeting/ calendar management• Ability to innovate and streamline processes in ever-changing environments• Ability to type 50 wpm with accuracy in spelling, punctuation &amp; grammar• Positive attitude with the ability to promote a positive environment• Experience sourcing, pricing and placing supply orders, and managing relationships with vendors. • A valid driver’s license Preferred candidate will have:o Business Administration certificate, Administration Assistant training or equivalento Administrative experience in an office environmentThis position falls under the provisions of the Collective Agreement with the BC Government and Service Employees' Union, Local 705. The placement of the Administrative &amp; Support Services Assistant is at Pay Grade 9, which is $27.60 to $30.52 per hour and a competitive comprehensive benefits package being offered.Applications must include a cover letter and a resume outlining your qualifications and experience. Careers - Thompson-Nicola Regional District (tnrd.ca)Thank you for considering the Thompson-Nicola Regional District as a place to share your talents!While we appreciate the interest of all applicants, only those candidates under consideration will be contacted. Compensation 27.60 - 30.52 Closes: 15 May, 2023 Thompson-Nicola Regional Library Kamloops , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
