Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Learning Services Librarian Kelowna , BC Description OKANAGAN COLLEGEOkanagan College transforms lives and communities. We are one of Canada's leading colleges. We create outstanding educational experiences for our learners, both students and employees. We work and learn in a welcoming and caring culture. We are a catalyst for change through collaboration with our learners and partners. We serve, lead and anticipate the social, economic and environmental needs of communities.Position Title:Learning Services LibrarianCompetition Number:C002363Division/Portfolio:Library ServicesDepartment/Program:LibraryCampus/Centre:KelownaYour Opportunity:Under the general direction of the Director of Library Services, is responsible for liaison with the International Education and English Language (EL) departments, and one or more other instructional departments, works with other Library and College employees and departments as appropriate to develop students’ academic skills related to plagiarism, citation, and academic integrity Other duties include reference, library research instruction, collection development, professional development, service, and may include scholarly activity.Education and Experience:Minimum qualification is a degree from an accredited Master’s program in library and information studies.Recent experience in an academic library, including experience in the provision of library instruction and reference servicesExperience assisting library users with both print and electronic resources, including creating instructional materials in a variety of formatsRecent experience working with International and/or students whose first language is not English is preferredExperience working or studying in an international setting would be an assetFunctions and Duties:1. Acts as liaison to the International Education department2. Acts as liaison to the EL department and other instructional departments as appropriate, to ensure that library collections and services meet the needs of students, and prepares course/program collection assessments and program review/accreditation Library reports for liaison departments3. Works closely with the Kelowna Campus Librarian to meet the library and information needs of International students, including study tour students, on the Kelowna campus4. Provides reference services, in person, by email, and in a real time virtual environment5. Prepares and delivers instruction to students, in person and in a virtual environment in conjunction with the Kelowna campus librarian and other librarians6. Works with Kelowna Learning Centre staff and other OC employees as appropriate to develop students’ academic skills related to plagiarism, citation, and academic integrity using a variety of instructional methods7. Provides support for instruction and other library services related to International and EL students and programs on campuses outside Kelowna8. Prepares research guides and tutorials, and guides to the use of Library collections and services, using a variety of media and formats9. Participates in the development of the Library collection by working with the Collections and Cataloguing Librarian and departmental Library representatives to plan for resource needs and to select books, media and other materials10. Contributes to planning and development of Library policies and procedures by participating in the Library Management Committee11. Engages in professional development activity intended to promote subject area and technical competence in library and information science and teaching and learning12. Engages in service activities that support the College and/or the profession and/or the community13. If requested and approved, may engage in scholarly activity, which may include scholarship, research and creative activity14. Performs other related librarian duties as assigned.15. Some evening and weekend work may be required.Skills and Abilities:- Familiar with, and supportive of, new and emerging technologies in library services and instructional settings.- Strong oral and written communication skills.- Ability to facilitate communication and connections among students and faculty.- Ability to work independently, and as part of a team, to assist in the delivery of library services.- Ability to recognize, respect and work effectively with people of diverse educational and socio­cultural backgrounds, including International and EL students.- Strong organizational skills in managing multiple activities and working under time constraints.- Demonstrated ability to learn new skills.- Demonstrated ability to teach in a variety of situations, across a diversity of subjects and program levels, and using a variety of methods, including active learning.Appointment Type:Faculty - Full-time TermAppointment Start Date:08/21/2023Appointment End Date:08/20/2024Schedule:35 hours per week, Monday through Friday; some evening and weekend work may be required from time to timeAnnual Salary/Hourly Rate:Salary range $62,828 to $100,958 with normal starting salary between $69,017 and $75,206 annually*, dependent on relevant education and experience. *Note: Part-time Term and summer appointments subject to adjustment factors as per the collective agreementPosting Opening Date:04/27/2023Posting Closing Date:05/22/2023APPLICATIONS:To apply for this position, please go to our employment site: https://www.employmentopportunities.okanagan.bc.ca and complete an on-line application. All applications must be submitted through our employment site to be considered.Okanagan College is committed to increasing the equitable and inclusive participation of marginalized people in all aspects of college life. We welcome and encourage applications from Indigenous Peoples, Black People, members of racialized groups/visible minorities, people with disabilities and people with diverse gender identities or expressions. People with disabilities who anticipate needing accommodations for any part of the application process may contact, in confidence, AccessibilityHR@okanagan.bc.ca Compensation Salary range $62,828 to $100,958 with normal starting salary between $69,017 and $75,206 annually*, dependent on relevant education and experience. *Note: Part-time Term and summer appointments subject to adjustment factors as per the collective agreement Closes: 22 May, 2023 Okanagan College Kelowna , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
