Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Museum Interpreter Town of the Blue Mountains , ON Description The Museum Interpreter is responsible for all promotional needs of the organization, as well as participation in the development of all Communications Plans, Strategic Plans, branding and marketing strategies, and communication consultation planning.The Museum Interpreter is a front-line service staff who provides a variety of technical services to the Curator and community museum, a Branch of the Blue Mountains Public Library, in the areas of Collection Management. Duties include digitizing, cataloguing, photographing and storage of artifacts; data entry; exhibition research and development, preparation and mounting; community outreach and programs using the collection and other related resources. This candidate will provide direct service to Museum patrons including tours, library circulation, and delivery of Museum programs as required and assist with BMPL program delivery consistent with the policies, practices and procedures of the organization.Key areas of this position:Cover Customer Service Desk including circulation of materials, greeter, sales, and phone/email;Provide tours of the facility and answer collections on exhibits held in the public spaces and online;Digitization of collections;Artifact and Archive cataloguing including data entry, photography, condition reporting, etc., and assist with Collections Management;Safe, secure storage of artifacts, record environmental readings, and provide preventative conservation;Assist with receiving and shipments of exhibitions;Exhibit research, development, preparation and mounting;Assist with donations to the collection including liaising with donors;Planning, delivering and promoting exhibits, including community exhibits and programs, in coordination with the Curator and Library Programming staff;Conduct Museum programs and special events, and assist with Library programs;Liaise with community groups, historical societies, etc. to promote partnerships regarding exhibits, the collection, etc.;Provide presentations and tours as required;Assist with research requests, and provide Tourism services;Assists patrons with information and multi- level reference questions and basic computer assistance;Display and promote positive “Team Player” attitudes and actions. This includes positive communications with supervisors and other Town staff regarding ideas and initiatives to enhance the workplace improve policies, procedures and services;Communicate with the public in an effective and courteous manner regarding programs, policies, and procedures of the museum and the library.Job DetailsHours of Work: This is a part-time position at the Craigleith Heritage Depot and will include regular weekend shifts and occasional weekday shifts, between 7-14 hours per week. Multiple candidates will be considered to meet all shift requirements. This is a great position for those who are in school or working elsewhere weekdays!Education and Experience:Postsecondary degree or diploma requiredMinimum of 1 year experience in customer service, with museum, archives, or library preferred.Experience with data entry, with Industry standard software such as PastPerfect, Integrated Library Systems, OLS database searches preferred.Material Culture Heritage Knowledge, skills and abilities an asset;Interest and willingness to learn cultural history surrounding collections and region a must.PastPerfect an asset.Information for Interested Candidates:Click to Open: Full Job DescriptionThe submission deadline for applications is 4:00 p.m. on May 11, 2023 EST. Submissions must be made via the following link: https://www.thebluemountains.ca/form/human-resourc...Salary Range: Grade 4 on the 2023 Salary Grid. Compensation $21.62 Closes: 11 May, 2023 The Blue Mountains Public Library Town of the Blue Mountains , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
