Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Branch Head - Savona Library Kamloops , BC Description About the Thompson-Nicola Regional DistrictEncompassing an unparalleled geographic region in the heart of British Columbia, the Thompson-Nicola Regional District (TNRD) offers the best of both worlds. Urban life within vibrant communities and outlying rural regions showcase the region's beauty: pristine but rugged mountains, rolling grasslands, lush evergreen forests and both historic and modern areas, all within approximately 45,000 square kilometres. Headquartered in the City of Kamloops, the TNRD provides a wide range of local government services to a population of 151,086 located within its 11 diverse municipalities and 10 electoral areas. Savona is a small community located at the west end of Kamloops Lake, approximately 45 km. from Kamloops. Savona and the nearby community of Tobiano are surrounded by semi-arid grasslands and hills, which support cattle ranching and agriculture. The area is popular with outdoor enthusiasts for boating, hiking, golfing, and mountain biking. The area population is approximately 650. Our Library SystemThe Thompson-Nicola Regional Library (TNRL), the largest department of the Regional District provides services through 12 locations and a Mobile Library. Located in the Central Interior of British Columbia, the TNRL is committed to providing excellent service to patrons for lifetime personal growth, learning and enjoyment. The Library team provides programming, materials and resources to people of all ages and abilities. The Branch Head will work in an organization that values flexibility and exemplary service. As a member of the TNRL, you will help to build strong relationships and partnerships in all of our communities. The RoleThe TNRL is seeking a permanent part-time Branch Head for the Savona Library who will create a welcoming environment and a superb library experience for all. The Branch Head will help patrons of all ages with circulation, reference, readers’ advisory and technology questions. The Branch Head will also be responsible for creating, organizing and delivering programs for children, young adults and adults. The Branch Head completes cash reconciliation, approves timesheets and assists with staff scheduling, facility and safety inspections, routine reports and statistics. Outside of the scheduled hours of operation, the Branch Head will deliver and participate in staff training, meetings, system projects and initiatives, and offer outreach programs or attend community events. The Branch Head will develop and maintain effective relationships with staff, patrons and the community through excellent interpersonal and communication skills. Travel may be required for meetings and/or professional development. There is a physical component to the position as library staff stand or walk for the entirety of the shift; move, pack and unpack delivery bins, check in and shelve library materials, regular keyboarding, as well as other duties. JOB REQUIREMENTSThe Ideal Candidate will have: A passion for helping others and a belief in the importance of literacy Minimum two-year certificate/diploma from an accredited post-secondary institutionExperience in developing and delivering programs to all agesA commitment to ongoing learning and professional developmentExceptional technical skills and aptitude including but not limited to:Knowledge of Windows, Android and iOS operating systemsDemonstrated skill using Microsoft Office ProgramsAbility to operate peripheral equipment such as printers, e-reader, tablets, ebooks/eaudiobooks, and a variety of smartphonesExcellent customer service skills and the ability to handle challenging situations Supervisory skillsAttention to detail Ability to work independently; ability to work in a team environment to participate in system-wide programs and initiativesValid driver's licenseThe position is subject to the provisions of the Collective Agreement with the BC General Employees’ Union, local 705.This is a Grid 10 position, step 1 pay rate is $26.20 per hour. Non-benefitted staff will receive an additional percentage in lieu of benefits.The Branch Head works a rotating schedule. Week 1 is 16 scheduled hours plus one hour of unscheduled administration time; week 2 is 12 scheduled hours plus one unscheduled hour of administration time. The schedule is subject to change based on operational need. Additional hours may be scheduled for meetings/training purposes. The TNRL requires that all successful applicants undergo a Criminal Record Check. Interested applicants should apply with a resume and cover letter. Careers - Thompson-Nicola Regional District (tnrd.ca) Compensation 26.20 - 29.05 Closes: 16 May, 2023 Thompson-Nicola Regional Library Kamloops , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
