eds and to select books, media and other materials14. Contributes to planning and development of Library policies and procedures by participating in the Library Management Committee15. Engages in professional development activity intended to promote subject area and technical competence in librarianship and information science16. Engages in service activities that support the College and/or the profession and/or the community17. If requested and approved, may engage in scholarly activity, which may include scholarship, research and creative activity18. Other related librarian duties.Skills and Abilities:Familiar with, and supportive of, new and emerging technologies in library servicesStrong oral and written communication skillsAbility to promote contact and communication among students and facultyAbility to work independently, and as part of a team, to assist in the delivery of library servicesAbility to work with people of diverse educational and socio-cultural backgroundsStrong organizational skills in managing multiple activities and working under time constraintsDemonstrated ability to learn new skillsDemonstrated ability to teach in a variety of situations, across a diversity of subjects and program levels, and using a variety of methods, including active learningSome evening and weekend work may be required.Appointment Type:Faculty - Full-time ContinuingAppointment Start Date:08/08/2023Schedule:35 hours per week, Monday through FridaySome evening and weekend work may be required from time to time.Annual Salary/Hourly Rate:Salary range $62,828 to $100,958 with normal starting salary between $69,017 and $75,206 annually*, dependent on relevant education and experience. *Note: Part-time Term and summer appointments subject to adjustment factors as per Collective Agreement.Posting Opening Date:04/24/2023Posting Closing Date:05/22/2023APPLICATIONS:To apply for this position, please go to our employment site: https://www.employmentopportunities.okanagan.bc.ca and complete an on-line application. All applications must be submitted through our employment site to be considered.Okanagan College is committed to increasing the equitable and inclusive participation of marginalized people in all aspects of college life. We welcome and encourage applications from Indigenous Peoples, Black People, members of racialized groups/visible minorities, people with disabilities and people with diverse gender identities or expressions. People with disabilities who anticipate needing accommodations for any part of the application process may contact, in confidence, AccessibilityHR@okanagan.bc.ca Compensation Salary range $62,828 to $100,958 with normal starting salary between $69,017 and $75,206 annually*, dependent on relevant education and experience. *Note: Part-time Term and summer appointments subject to adjustment factors as per Collective Agreement. Closes: 22 May, 2023 Okanagan College Kelowna , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
